Providing a perfect illustration of just how much Los Angeles remains a sanctuary city, KFI AM640 reports that of the 300 Immigration and Customs Enforcement [ICE] requests to detain “individuals who had been arrested on suspicion of local crimes and had been flagged in law enforcement databases for immigration violations or warrants” the Los Angeles Police Department agreed to do so exactly zero times. 
L.A. Mayor Eric Garcetti has said the LAPD would comply only with ICE requests when a warrant was criminal and involved serious crimes. 
